{"type":"message","id":"25aaa858","parentId":"da034c67","timestamp":"2026-04-20T14:13:34.081Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is clear - the Ventoy drive path variable isn't being properly expanded when we `cd /tmp`. The script changes directory to `/tmp` but then tries to access `$VENTOY/*.zip` which becomes relative. Also, many of these zip files failed to extract (unzip can't find them).\n\nLet me write a cleaner script that:\n1. Uses absolute paths throughout\n2. Properly handles the variable scoping issue\n3. Actually extracts each file correctly from the Ventoy drive\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"267539880","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/install_ventoy_skills.sh","content":"#!/bin/bash\n# Install skills from Ventoy USB drive to OpenClaw workspace\n\nVENTOY=\"/media/kensoulstar/Ventoy/zwd/skills\"\nWORKSPACE=\"/home/kensoulstar/.openclaw/workspace\"\nSKILLS_DIR=\"$WORKSPACE/skills\"\nTMPDIR=\"/tmp/ventoy-skills-$$\"\n\necho \"=== Installing skills from Ventoy USB ===\"\necho \"Source: $VENTOY\"\necho \"Target: $SKILLS_DIR\"\necho \"\"\n\n# Create temp extraction directory\nmkdir -p \"$TMPDIR\"\n\nfor zipfile in \"$VENTOY\"/*.zip; do\n  filename=$(basename \"$zipfile\")\n  \n  # Skip archives we've already handled\n  if [[ \"$filename\" == *\"skills-main\"* ]] || [[ \"$filename\" == *\"openclaw-workspace\"* ]]; then\n    echo \"⊘ $filename (skipped - archive)\"\n    continue\n  fi\n  \n  # Create extraction directory for this zip\n  extract_dir=\"$TMPDIR/$$(echo \"$filename\" | sed 's/\\..*//')\"\n  mkdir -p \"$extract_dir\"\n  \n  # Extract to temp directory\n  if ! unzip -q \"$zipfile\" -d \"$extract_dir\" 2>/dev/null; then\n    echo \"? $filename: extraction failed (corrupted?)\"\n    continue\n  fi\n  \n  # Find SKILL.md files in extracted content\n  skill_dirs=$(find \"$extract_dir\" -name \"SKILL.md\" | xargs dirname 2>/dev/null)\n  \n  if [ -z \"$skill_dirs\" ]; then\n    echo \"? $filename: no SKILL.md found after extraction\"\n    ls \"$extract_dir/\" 2>/dev/null | head -5\n  else\n    for dir in $skill_dirs; do\n      name=$(basename \"$dir\")\n      existing_skill=\"$SKILLS_DIR/$name/SKILL.md\"\n      \n      if [ ! -f \"$existing_skill\" ]; then\n        cp -r \"$dir\" \"$SKILLS_DIR/\" && echo \"✓ $name (from $filename)\" || \\\n          echo \"? $name: copy failed\"\n      else\n        # Compare SKILL.md content to check for updates\n        tmp_md5=$(md5sum \"$dir/SKILL.md\" 2>/dev/null | cut -d' ' -f1)\n        exist_md5=$(md5sum \"$existing_skill\" 2>/dev/null | cut -d' ' -f1)\n        if [ \"$tmp_md5\" != \"$exist_md5\" ]; then\n          cp -r \"$dir\" \"$SKILLS_DIR/\" && echo \"~ $name (updated)\" || \\\n            echo \"? $name: update failed\"\n        else\n          echo \"- $name already up-to-date\"\n        fi\n      fi\n    done\n  fi\n  \n  # Cleanup this extraction\n  rm -rf \"$extract_dir\"\ndone\n\n# Cleanup temp directory\nrm -rf \"$TMPDIR\"\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== Final skill count ===\" \nls \"$SKILLS_DIR/\" | wc -l\necho \"\"\necho \"Installed skills:\"\nls \"$SKILLS_DIR/\""}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"lmstudio","model":"qwen3.6-35b-a3b-claude-4.6-opus-reasoning-distilled@q4_k_m","usage":{"input":68643,"output":938,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":69581,"cost":{"input":0.137286,"output":0.011256,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.14854199999999998}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776694369657,"responseId":"chatcmpl-51tjgojycmrtlqxqtg8ua"}}
