{"type":"message","id":"1022da37","parentId":"ead53169","timestamp":"2026-04-20T14:14:40.980Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The script has issues - the `find` command is returning too many results including `.`, and the sed expression for extracting directory names isn't working properly in bash. The zip files are being extracted but without finding proper SKILL.md structures.\n\nLet me rewrite this more carefully:\n1. First extract each zip to a temp dir\n2. Look for SKILL.md files at various depths\n3. Properly name the skill directories based on what's inside\n4. Clean up properly after processing each file\n\nThe main issues I see:\n- `find \"$extract_dir\" -name \"SKILL.md\"` is finding files in /tmp subdirectories too (systemd-private etc.)\n\n\n- The sed pattern for extracting names from paths isn't working correctly\n- Many of these zip files don't follow the standard OpenClaw skill structure with SKILL.md\n\nI need to fix these issues and rewrite the extraction logic.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n脚本有些问题，让我重写一个更可靠的版本：\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"802039255","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/install_ventoy_v2.sh","content":"#!/bin/bash\n# Install skills from Ventoy USB drive to OpenClaw workspace\n\nVENTOY=\"/media/kensoulstar/Ventoy/zwd/skills\"\nWORKSPACE=\"/home/kensoulstar/.openclaw/workspace\"\nSKILLS_DIR=\"$WORKSPACE/skills\"\nTMPBASE=\"/tmp/vskill-$$\"\n\necho \"=== Installing skills from Ventoy USB ===\"\necho \"Source: $VENTOY\"\necho \"Target: $SKILLS_DIR\"\necho \"\"\n\nmkdir -p \"$TMPDIR_BASE\" 2>/dev/null || mkdir -p \"$TMPBASE\"\nTMPDIR=\"$TMPBASE\"\n\nfor zipfile in \"$VENTOY\"/*.zip; do\n  filename=$(basename \"$zipfile\")\n  \n  # Skip archives we've already handled\n  if [[ \"$filename\" == *\"skills-main\"* ]] || [[ \"$filename\" == *\"openclaw-workspace\"* ]]; then\n    echo \"⊘ $filename (skipped)\"\n    continue\n  fi\n  \n  # Create extraction directory for this zip\n  extract_dir=\"$TMPDIR/$$(basename \"$filename\" .zip | tr -d '0-9.-_')\"\n  mkdir -p \"$extract_dir\"\n  \n  # Extract to temp directory\n  if ! unzip -q \"$zipfile\" -d \"$extract_dir\" 2>/dev/null; then\n    echo \"? $filename: extraction failed\"\n    rm -rf \"$extract_dir\"\n    continue\n  fi\n  \n  # Find SKILL.md files in extracted content (limit depth to avoid /tmp noise)\n  skill_md_files=$(find \"$extract_dir\" -maxdepth 5 -name \"SKILL.md\" 2>/dev/null | grep -v \"^$TMPDIR\")\n  \n  if [ -z \"$skill_md_files\" ]; then\n    echo \"? $filename: no SKILL.md found\"\n    ls \"$extract_dir/\" 2>/dev/null | head -3\n    rm -rf \"$extract_dir\"\n    continue\n  fi\n  \n  for skill_md in $skill_md_files; do\n    skill_dir=$(dirname \"$skill_md\")\n    skill_name=$(basename \"$skill_dir\")\n    \n    # If no proper name found, derive from zip filename\n    if [ \"$skill_name\" = \".\" ] || [ -z \"$skill_name\" ]; then\n      skill_name=$(echo \"$filename\" | sed 's/_[0-9]*\\.[0-9]*\\.[0-9]*//; s/-[0-9]*\\.[0-9]*\\.[0-9]*//')\n    fi\n    \n    existing_skill=\"$SKILLS_DIR/$skill_name/SKILL.md\"\n    \n    if [ ! -f \"$existing_skill\" ]; then\n      cp -r \"$skill_dir\" \"$SKILLS_DIR/\" && echo \"✓ $skill_name (from $filename)\" || \\\n        echo \"? $skill_name: copy failed\"\n    else\n      tmp_md5=$(md5sum \"$skill_md\" 2>/dev/null | cut -d' ' -f1)\n      exist_md5=$(md5sum \"$existing_skill\" 2>/dev/null | cut -d' ' -f1)\n      if [ \"$tmp_md5\" != \"$exist_md5\" ]; then\n        cp -r \"$skill_dir\" \"$SKILLS_DIR/\" && echo \"~ $skill_name (updated)\" || \\\n          echo \"? $skill_name: update failed\"\n      else\n        echo \"- $skill_name up-to-date\"\n      fi\n    fi\n  done\n  \n  rm -rf \"$extract_dir\"\ndone\n\nrm -rf \"$TMPBASE\"\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== Final count ===\" \nls \"$SKILLS_DIR/\" | grep -v \"^AGENTS\\|^BOOTSTRAP\\|^HEARTBEAT\\|^IDENTITY\\|^SOUL\\|^TOOLS\\|^USER\\|^MEMORY\\|^memory\\|^state\\|^skills\\|\\.md$\\|\\.ps1\\|\\.csv\\|\\.jsonc\\|OpenClaw_\\|^技能\" | wc -l"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"lmstudio","model":"qwen3.6-35b-a3b-claude-4.6-opus-reasoning-distilled@q4_k_m","usage":{"input":73179,"output":1304,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":74483,"cost":{"input":0.146358,"output":0.015648,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.16200599999999998}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776694443266,"responseId":"chatcmpl-z4lhscu7mn4d01pwapj9s"}}
