{"type":"message","id":"6cda8ebf","parentId":"36c89b39","timestamp":"2026-04-20T14:15:01.683Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, I have a bug in the script - `mkdir -p \"$TMPDIR_BASE\"` won't work since `$TMPDIR_BASE` isn't defined. Let me fix that and also address the issue with finding SKILL.md files properly.\n\nActually, looking at this more carefully, the main issue is:\n1. The find command is picking up /tmp system directories\n2. The extraction directory names aren't being cleaned up properly\n3. Many of these zip files don't follow the standard skill structure\n\n\nI should simplify this entirely and just process each file directly without worrying about all the edge cases.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"338413426","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Let me try a more direct approach - extract each zip manually and check its contents\ncd /home/kensoulstar/.openclaw/workspace/skills && \\\nVENTOY=\"/media/kensoulstar/Ventoy/zwd/skills\"\n\nfor zipfile in \"$VENTOY\"/*.zip; do\n  fname=$(basename \"$zipfile\")\n  \n  # Skip archives\n  if [[ \"$fname\" == *\"skills-main\"* ]] || [[ \"$fname\" == *\"openclaw-workspace\"* ]]; then\n    continue\n  fi\n  \n  # Extract to /tmp with unique name\n  extname=\"vs_$(echo $fname | tr -d '._-')\"\n  rm -rf \"/tmp/$extname\" 2>/dev/null\n  unzip -q \"$zipfile\" -d \"/tmp/$extname\" 2>&1 >/dev/null\n  \n  # Check for SKILL.md at various levels\n  found=$(find \"/tmp/$extname\" -maxdepth 4 -name \"SKILL.md\" 2>/dev/null | head -3)\n  \n  if [ -n \"$found\" ]; then\n    skill_dir=$(dirname \"$(echo $found | head -1)\")\n    skill_name=$(basename \"$skill_dir\")\n    \n    # Skip if extracted dir is the zip name itself (not a proper skill folder structure)\n    if [ \"$skill_name\" != \".\" ] && [ ! -d \"skills/$skill_name\" ]; then\n      cp -r \"$skill_dir\" \"skills/\" 2>/dev/null && echo \"✓ $skill_name (from $fname)\" || \\\n        # Try extracting the entire extracted directory as a skill\n        if [ ! -d \"$skill_name\" ]; then\n          cp -r \"/tmp/$extname\" \"$skill_name\" 2>/dev/null && echo \"✓ $skill_name (full extract from $fname)\"\n        fi\n    elif [ ! -d \"skills/$skill_name\" ] && [ \"$skill_name\" = \".\" ]; then\n      # The extracted dir itself might be the skill name\n      for d in /tmp/$extname/*/; do\n        if [ -f \"$d/SKILL.md\" ]; then\n          name=$(basename $d)\n          cp -r \"$d\" \"skills/\" 2>/dev/null && echo \"✓ $name (from $fname)\"\n        fi\n      done\n    fi\n    rm -rf \"/tmp/$extname\"\n  else\n    # List what's inside for debugging\n    ls \"/tmp/$extname/\" | head -3\n  fi\n  \ndone\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== Total skills ===\" \nls skills/ | wc -l","timeout":180}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"lmstudio","model":"qwen3.6-35b-a3b-claude-4.6-opus-reasoning-distilled@q4_k_m","usage":{"input":74327,"output":861,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":75188,"cost":{"input":0.14865399999999998,"output":0.010332000000000001,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.158986}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776694481183,"responseId":"chatcmpl-jwv5q93a5vdzx9jqshymzq"}}
