{"type":"message","id":"dcf334a4","parentId":"e3fa4e16","timestamp":"2026-04-20T14:15:56.794Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see what happened - the previous script created some junk directories but they're at the workspace level, not inside skills/. The vs_* directories don't exist because they weren't created properly. Let me check if there are any uninstalled skills from the Ventoy drive that I missed.\n\nLooking back at my output:\n- 14 individual skills were installed (douyin-downloader-nodejs, douyin-video-analyst, etc.)\n- But these have long names and weren't renamed properly\n\nLet me check if those directories exist somewhere or if they were extracted differently. Actually, looking more carefully at the output - it says \"✓ vs_douyindownloadernodejs100zip\" but then when I checked for vs_* directories, none were found. \n\nThe extraction likely failed silently because the zip files got extracted to /tmp instead of being copied into the skills directory as intended.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"918202700","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check what actually needs to be installed from Ventoy\ncd /home/kensoulstar/.openclaw/workspace/skills && \\\nVENTOY=\"/media/kensoulstar/Ventoy/zwd/skills\"\n\necho \"=== Checking which Ventoy skills are NOT yet installed ===\" \nfor zipfile in \"$VENTOY\"/*.zip; do\n  fname=$(basename \"$zipfile\")\n  \n  # Skip archives we've handled\n  if [[ \"$fname\" == *\"skills-main\"* ]] || [[ \"$fname\" == *\"openclaw-workspace\"* ]]; then\n    continue\n  fi\n  \n  # Get skill name from filename\n  skill_name=$(echo \"$fname\" | sed 's/_[0-9]*\\.[0-9]*\\.[0-9]*//; s/-[0-9]*\\.[0-9]*\\.[0-9]*//')\n  \n  # Check if it exists as a proper skill directory with SKILL.md\n  if [ -d \"$skill_name\" ] && [ -f \"$skill_name/SKILL.md\" ]; then\n    echo \"- $fname: ALREADY INSTALLED ($skill_name)\"\n  else\n    echo \"? $fname: NOT FOUND (expected: $skill_name)\"\n  fi\ndone\n\n# Also check for the ones that were extracted with different names\necho \"\"\necho \"=== Checking for incorrectly named skills ===\" \nfor zipfile in \"$VENTOY\"/*.zip; do\n  fname=$(basename \"$zipfile\")\n  if [[ \"$fname\" == *\"skills-main\"* ]] || [[ \"$fname\" == *\"openclaw-workspace\"* ]]; then continue; fi\n  \n  skill_name=$(echo \"$fname\" | sed 's/_[0-9]*\\.[0-9]*\\.[0-9]*//; s/-[0-9]*\\.[0-9]*\\.[0-9]*//')\n  \n  # Check if any existing dir contains this name or is a match\n  for d in *; do\n    if [ -d \"$d\" ] && [ -f \"$d/SKILL.md\" ]; then\n      # Compare SKILL.md content with what would be extracted from zip\n      rm -rf \"/tmp/check_$d\" 2>/dev/null\n      unzip -q \"$zipfile\" -d \"/tmp/check_$d\" 2>/dev/null\n      found_md=$(find \"/tmp/check_$d\" -name \"SKILL.md\" | head -1)\n      if [ -n \"$found_md\" ]; then\n        existing_md5=$(md5sum \"$d/SKILL.md\" 2>/dev/null | cut -d' ' -f1)\n        new_md5=$(md5sum \"$found_md\" 2>/dev/null | cut -d' ' -f1)\n        if [ \"$existing_md5\" = \"$new_md5\" ]; then\n          echo \"- $fname: MATCHES existing '$d'\"\n        fi\n      fi\n    fi\n  done\n  rm -rf \"/tmp/check_\"* 2>/dev/null\ndone","timeout":180}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"lmstudio","model":"qwen3.6-35b-a3b-claude-4.6-opus-reasoning-distilled@q4_k_m","usage":{"input":77236,"output":1070,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":78306,"cost":{"input":0.154472,"output":0.01284,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.167312}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776694531602,"responseId":"chatcmpl-mzki6neb7uhmr0gq9x6m4a"}}
