{"type":"message","id":"5fa74cf0","parentId":"94e124ca","timestamp":"2026-04-20T14:16:44.442Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so the problem is clear - none of those 16 skill directories from Ventoy were actually installed properly. The previous script said \"✓\" but it didn't actually copy them because:\n1. The extracted directory names had underscores that got converted to something else\n2. The `cp` command failed silently\n\nLet me now do a proper extraction and installation of all these skills. I'll need to extract each one, find the SKILL.md content, determine what skill name it should have, and copy it over.\n\nI notice the previous run said things like:\n\n\n- ✓ vs_douyindownloadernodejs100zip (from douyin-downloader-nodejs-1.0.0.zip)\n- ✓ memory-lancedb-pro-skill-main (from memory-lancedb-pro-skill-main.zip)\n\nSo it seems like the extraction DID happen (it found SKILL.md), but the copy failed because I was trying to `cp -r \"$skill_dir\" \"skills/\"` and `$skill_dir` pointed to a directory inside /tmp that had just been cleaned up or didn't exist properly. The issue is that when extracting with `-d \"/tmp/$extname\"`, the extracted structure includes `/tmp/$extname/` as the root, so `dirname \"$(echo $found | head -1)\"` would give me something like `/tmp/vs_douyin...`, and then trying to copy from there fails because I'm not in the right context.\n\nLet me just do this step-by-step now with a clean approach instead of retrying the same thing.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"915101260","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Let me extract each zip properly and install them one by one\ncd /home/kensoulstar/.openclaw/workspace/skills && \\\nVENTOY=\"/media/kensoulstar/Ventoy/zwd/skills\"\n\nfor zipfile in \"$VENTOY\"/*.zip; do\n  fname=$(basename \"$zipfile\")\n  \n  # Skip archives we've handled\n  if [[ \"$fname\" == *\"skills-main\"* ]] || [[ \"$fname\" == *\"openclaw-workspace\"* ]]; then\n    continue\n  fi\n  \n  # Create extraction dir with unique name\n  extid=\"x_$(echo $RANDOM)\"\n  extract_dir=\"/tmp/extract_$extid\"\n  mkdir -p \"$extract_dir\"\n  \n  # Extract to temp directory\n  unzip -q \"$zipfile\" -d \"$extract_dir\" 2>/dev/null\n  \n  # Find SKILL.md files in extracted content\n  skill_md=$(find \"$extract_dir\" -maxdepth 4 -name \"SKILL.md\" 2>/dev/null | head -1)\n  \n  if [ -n \"$skill_md\" ]; then\n    skill_dir=$(dirname \"$skill_md\")\n    \n    # Determine the proper skill name from the zip filename\n    expected_name=$(echo \"$fname\" | sed 's/_[0-9]*\\.[0-9]*\\.[0-9]*//; s/-[0-9]*\\.[0-9]*\\.[0-9]*//' | tr -d '.')\n    \n    # Check if the extracted directory has its own name (like \"skills-main/skills/xxx\")\n    extracted_name=$(basename \"$skill_dir\")\n    \n    # Use expected name unless it's \".\" or empty\n    if [ \"$extracted_name\" != \".\" ] && [ ! -z \"$extracted_name\" ]; then\n      final_name=\"$extracted_name\"\n    else\n      final_name=\"$expected_name\"\n    fi\n    \n    # Install if not already present\n    if [ ! -d \"$final_name\" ] || [ ! -f \"$final_name/SKILL.md\" ]; then\n      cp -r \"$skill_dir\" \"./$final_name/\" 2>/dev/null && \\\n        echo \"✓ $final_name (from $fname)\" || \\\n        # Try as full extracted directory name\n        if [ ! -d \"$expected_name\" ]; then\n          cp -r \"$extract_dir\" \"./$expected_name/\" 2>/dev/null && \\\n            echo \"✓ $expected_name (full extract from $fname)\"\n        fi\n    else\n      # Check for updates via SKILL.md comparison\n      existing_md5=$(md5sum \"$final_name/SKILL.md\" 2>/dev/null | cut -d' ' -f1)\n      new_md5=$(md5sum \"$skill_md\" 2>/dev/null | cut -d' ' -f1)\n      if [ \"$existing_md5\" != \"$new_md5\" ]; then\n        cp -r \"$skill_dir\" \"./$final_name/\" 2>/dev/null && \\\n          echo \"~ $final_name (updated from $fname)\"\n      fi\n    fi\n  else\n    # No SKILL.md found, show contents for debugging\n    echo \"? $fname: no SKILL.md (contents: $(ls \"$extract_dir\" | head -3))\"\n  fi\n  \n  # Cleanup extraction directory\n  rm -rf \"$extract_dir\"\ndone\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== Final skill count ===\" \nfind . -maxdepth 1 -type d -name \"*\" | grep -v \"^\\.$\" | wc -l","timeout":300}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"lmstudio","model":"qwen3.6-35b-a3b-claude-4.6-opus-reasoning-distilled@q4_k_m","usage":{"input":78802,"output":1479,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":80281,"cost":{"input":0.157604,"output":0.017748,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.175352}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776694571986,"responseId":"chatcmpl-jy5vebuaaoc22691h2sdce"}}
