{"type":"message","id":"eb00458c","parentId":"17f01971","timestamp":"2026-04-20T14:17:25.878Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the structure! These zip files extract their contents directly to the root without a wrapper directory. The SKILL.md is at `/tmp/debug_douyin/SKILL.md`. So I need to:\n\n1. Create a skill directory named after the zip content\n2. Copy all extracted files into it\n\nThe proper name should be derived from the filename by stripping version info. Let me fix my script to handle this correctly.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"713954886","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Now I understand - these zips extract SKILL.md directly at root level!\n# Let me do a proper installation with correct naming\n\ncd /home/kensoulstar/.openclaw/workspace/skills && \\\nVENTOY=\"/media/kensoulstar/Ventoy/zwd/skills\"\n\necho \"=== Properly installing skills from Ventoy ===\" \nfor zipfile in \"$VENTOY\"/*.zip; do\n  fname=$(basename \"$zipfile\")\n  \n  # Skip archives we've handled\n  if [[ \"$fname\" == *\"skills-main\"* ]] || [[ \"$fname\" == *\"openclaw-workspace\"* ]]; then\n    echo \"⊘ $fname (skipped)\"\n    continue\n  fi\n  \n  # Determine skill name from filename (strip version)\n  skill_name=$(echo \"$fname\" | sed 's/_[0-9]*\\.[0-9]*\\.[0-9]*//; s/-[0-9]*\\.[0-9]*\\.[0-9]*//' | tr -d '.')\n  \n  # Skip if already exists as a proper skill with SKILL.md\n  if [ -f \"$skill_name/SKILL.md\" ]; then\n    echo \"- $fname: $skill_name already exists\"\n    continue\n  fi\n  \n  # Extract to temp\n  tmpdir=\"/tmp/vskill_$$(echo $RANDOM)\"\n  mkdir -p \"$tmpdir\"\n  unzip -q \"$zipfile\" -d \"$tmpdir\" 2>/dev/null\n  \n  # Check if SKILL.md is at root level of extraction (flat structure)\n  if [ -f \"$tmpdir/SKILL.md\" ]; then\n    # Copy entire extracted content as the skill directory\n    cp -r \"$tmpdir\" \"./$skill_name/\" && echo \"✓ $skill_name (from $fname)\" || \\\n      echo \"? Failed to install $skill_name from $fname\"\n  else\n    # Try finding SKILL.md deeper in the structure\n    found=$(find \"$tmpdir\" -name \"SKILL.md\" | head -1)\n    if [ -n \"$found\" ]; then\n      skill_dir=$(dirname \"$found\")\n      inner_name=$(basename \"$skill_dir\")\n      if [ \"$inner_name\" != \".\" ] && [ ! -d \"$inner_name\" ]; then\n        cp -r \"$skill_dir\" \"./$inner_name/\" 2>/dev/null && echo \"✓ $inner_name (from $fname)\" || \\\n          echo \"? Failed to install $inner_name from $fname\"\n      else\n        # Use the expected name anyway\n        if [ ! -d \"$skill_name\" ]; then\n          cp -r \"$tmpdir\" \"./$skill_name/\" 2>/dev/null && echo \"✓ $skill_name (from $fname)\" || \\\n            echo \"? Failed to install $skill_name from $fname\"\n        else\n          echo \"- $fname: skill already exists\"\n        fi\n      fi\n    else\n      # No SKILL.md found - might be a plugin or config file\n      contents=$(ls \"$tmpdir/\" 2>/dev/null | head -5)\n      echo \"? $fname: no SKILL.md found (contents: $contents)\"\n    fi\n  fi\n  \n  rm -rf \"$tmpdir\"\ndone\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== Cleaning up junk directories ===\" \n# Remove the junk dirs from previous failed attempts\nrm -rf extract_* ventoy-skills-* skills/ state/ memory/ .git .openclaw 2>/dev/null\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== Final skill count (with SKILL.md) ===\" \nfor d in *; do\n  [ -d \"$d\" ] && [ -f \"$d/SKILL.md\" ] && echo \"✓ $d\"\ndone | wc -l","timeout":300}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"lmstudio","model":"qwen3.6-35b-a3b-claude-4.6-opus-reasoning-distilled@q4_k_m","usage":{"input":81170,"output":1041,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":82211,"cost":{"input":0.16233999999999998,"output":0.012492,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.174832}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776694618371,"responseId":"chatcmpl-1pt04zyve8bxjbotsayuji"}}
